# AI SWARM ROBOTICS SPACE CLEANUP - Product Requirements Document

## 1\. Overview

**App Name:** AI SWARM ROBOTICS SPACE CLEANUP

AI SWARM ROBOTICS SPACE CLEANUP is a Progressive Web App (PWA) that serves as a virtual prototype and mission control center for autonomous space-cleaning robots designed to address the critical issue of space debris orbiting Earth. The application simulates a comprehensive space debris management system through advanced AI integration, real-time 3D visualization, and sensor simulation technologies including LiDAR, radar, magnetic detection, and vacuum-reverse systems.

**Target Audience:** Space technology researchers, aerospace engineers, educational institutions, government space agencies, environmental scientists, and technology enthusiasts interested in sustainable space operations. **Key Problems Solved:** Demonstrates feasible solutions for space debris cleanup without requiring physical hardware investment, provides realistic simulation of autonomous space robotics operations, offers comprehensive mission planning and monitoring capabilities, and showcases the potential of AI-driven space sustainability initiatives.

## 2\. Essential Core Features

* **3D Robot Visualization Engine** \- Real\-time 3D rendering of autonomous cleaning robots with camera integration and interactive controls
* **Mission Control Dashboard** \- Comprehensive command center with telemetry data\, system status\, and operational controls
* **Debris Detection & Classification System** \- AI\-powered identification and categorization of space debris objects
* **Sensor Simulation Suite** \- Virtual LiDAR\, radar\, magnetic\, and vacuum\-reverse sensor systems with realistic data output
* **GPS Tracking & Navigation** \- Real\-time positioning\, orbital tracking\, and trajectory visualization
* **Path Planning Algorithm** \- Automated route optimization for shortest and safest debris collection paths
* **Health Monitoring System** \- Robot diagnostics\, performance metrics\, and predictive maintenance alerts
* **Self-Repair Simulation** \- Automated maintenance cycles and repair protocol demonstrations
* **Virtual Astronaut Mode** \- First\-person perspective control allowing direct robot interaction
* **Real-time Data Analytics** \- Mission statistics\, efficiency metrics\, and performance reporting
* **Communication System** \- Simulated space\-to\-ground communication with delay modeling
* **Environmental Mapping** \- 3D orbital environment reconstruction and hazard identification
* **Mission Planning Interface** \- Pre\-mission setup\, objective configuration\, and timeline management
* **Emergency Response Protocols** \- Automated safety procedures and crisis management systems
* **Multi-Robot Coordination** \- Swarm robotics management and collaborative task assignment

## 3\. Tech Stack

**Front-End:** React, Tailwind CSS & Vite
**Back-End:** Supabase (authentication, database, storage, real-time capabilities)
**AI Integration:** OpenAI GPT-4o for debris classification, natural language mission commands, and intelligent decision-making algorithms
**APIs & Integrations:**

* Three.js or React Three Fiber for 3D visualization
* WebGL for advanced graphics rendering
* WebRTC for real-time communication simulation
* Orbital mechanics calculation libraries
* Geospatial APIs for Earth and orbital positioning
* Chart.js for data visualization and analytics

**Technical Requirements:**

* PWA capabilities with offline functionality
* WebGL support for 3D rendering
* Real-time data synchronization
* High-performance computing for physics simulations
* WebSocket connections for live telemetry

## 4\. Design Preferences

**Interface:** Futuristic space-themed design with dark backgrounds, holographic-style elements, and high-tech dashboard aesthetics reminiscent of NASA mission control centers.

**Color Palette:**

* Primary: Deep Space Blue (#0B1426)
* Secondary: Electric Cyan (#00F5FF)
* Accent: Warning Orange (#FF6B35)
* Supporting colors: Metallic Silver (#C0C0C0), Success Green (#00FF88)

**Typography:**

* Headings: Orbitron or similar sci-fi geometric font
* Body text: Inter or Roboto for optimal readability

**Design Considerations:** High contrast for mission-critical readability, responsive grid layouts for multi-monitor setups, accessibility compliance for professional environments, and smooth animations for 3D interactions.

## 5\. All Screens/Pages

### `/login` \- Authentication Screen

* **UI Elements:** Logo, username/email input field, password input field, login button, forgot password link, create account link
* **Navigation:** Entry point from app launch, routes to `/dashboard` on successful login
* **Conditional Elements:** Loading spinner during authentication, error messages for failed attempts

### `/dashboard` \- Mission Control Center

* **UI Elements:** Navigation header, real-time status cards, 3D robot viewport, telemetry panels, mission timeline, system alerts bar, quick action buttons
* **Navigation:** Main hub accessible from all screens, routes to specific modules via navigation menu
* **Conditional Elements:** Alert notifications, robot status indicators, live data streams

### `/robots` \- Robot Fleet Management

* **UI Elements:** Robot list with status cards, health indicators, deployment controls, robot selection buttons, performance metrics charts, maintenance schedules
* **Navigation:** Accessible from dashboard navigation, routes to `/robots/:id` for individual robot details
* **Conditional Elements:** Robot availability status, maintenance alerts, deployment readiness indicators

### `/robots/:id` \- Individual Robot Control

* **UI Elements:** Large 3D robot model, camera feed simulation, control joystick interface, sensor data panels, diagnostic information, manual override controls
* **Navigation:** Accessed from robot fleet page, includes back navigation and emergency stop button
* **Conditional Elements:** Control availability based on robot status, emergency alerts, sensor readings

### `/missions` \- Mission Planning Interface

* **UI Elements:** Mission creation form, objective selection dropdown, timeline builder, risk assessment panel, resource allocation interface, mission history list
* **Navigation:** Accessible from main navigation, routes to `/missions/:id` for active missions
* **Conditional Elements:** Mission status badges, approval workflows, scheduling conflicts

### `/missions/:id` \- Active Mission Monitoring

* **UI Elements:** Real-time mission map, progress tracking bars, live telemetry feeds, communication logs, abort mission button, objective completion checklist
* **Navigation:** Accessible from missions list, includes mission control tools and communication interface
* **Conditional Elements:** Mission phase indicators, critical alerts, completion status updates

### `/debris` \- Debris Database & Analysis

* **UI Elements:** Debris catalog with images, classification filters, threat level indicators, collection status, 3D debris field visualization, search functionality
* **Navigation:** Accessible from main navigation, routes to `/debris/:id` for detailed debris information
* **Conditional Elements:** Classification confidence levels, collection priority indicators, tracking accuracy status

### `/debris/:id` \- Detailed Debris Information

* **UI Elements:** High-resolution debris imagery, classification details, orbital parameters, collection difficulty rating, historical tracking data, collection strategy recommendations
* **Navigation:** Accessed from debris database, includes back navigation and related debris suggestions
* **Conditional Elements:** AI confidence ratings, collection feasibility assessments, risk warnings

### `/analytics` \- Performance Analytics Dashboard

* **UI Elements:** Performance metrics charts, efficiency graphs, mission success rates, cost analysis, environmental impact indicators, comparative analytics
* **Navigation:** Accessible from main navigation, includes filtering and date range selection
* **Conditional Elements:** Data availability indicators, trend analysis, predictive insights

### `/simulation` \- Virtual Training Environment

* **UI Elements:** Simulation scenario selector, difficulty settings, virtual environment controls, training objectives, performance scoring, replay functionality
* **Navigation:** Accessible from main navigation, routes to simulation environments
* **Conditional Elements:** Simulation status indicators, performance feedback, training progress tracking

### `/settings` \- Configuration & Preferences

* **UI Elements:** User profile settings, notification preferences, system configuration options, API key management, display preferences, backup/restore options
* **Navigation:** Accessible from user menu, includes save/cancel actions
* **Conditional Elements:** Setting validation messages, change confirmations, system status indicators

### `/help` \- Documentation & Support

* **UI Elements:** Help categories, search functionality, tutorial videos, FAQ sections, contact support form, system requirements information
* **Navigation:** Accessible from all screens via help icon, includes nested topic navigation
* **Conditional Elements:** Context-sensitive help content, tutorial progress tracking

## 6\. App Menu and Navigation Structure

**Navigation System:** Bottom tab bar navigation optimized for PWA mobile experience with hamburger menu for secondary features.

**Primary Navigation (Bottom Tab Bar):**

* Dashboard (Home icon)
* Robots (Robot icon)
* Missions (Target icon)
* Analytics (Chart icon)
* More (Menu icon)

**Secondary Navigation (Hamburger Menu under "More"):**

* Debris Database
* Simulation Center
* Settings
* Help & Support
* User Profile
* Logout

**Navigation Hierarchy:**

```
Dashboard (Main Hub)
├── Robots
│   └── Individual Robot Control
├── Missions
│   ├── Mission Planning
│   └── Active Mission Monitoring
├── Analytics
│   ├── Performance Reports
│   └── System Metrics
└── More Menu
    ├── Debris Database
    │   └── Debris Details
    ├── Simulation Center
    ├── Settings
    ├── Help
    └── Profile
```

**User Navigation Flow:** Users can quickly switch between primary functions via bottom navigation, access detailed views through progressive disclosure, and utilize the hamburger menu for advanced features and configuration options.

## 7\. User Flow

1. **App Launch & Authentication**
    * User opens PWA and lands on login screen
    * Enters credentials and authenticates via Supabase
    * App redirects to mission control dashboard
2. **Dashboard Overview**
    * User views real-time system status and active missions
    * Reviews alert notifications and system health indicators
    * Accesses quick actions for immediate robot control needs
3. **Robot Fleet Management**
    * User navigates to robots section via bottom tab
    * Reviews fleet status and selects specific robot for detailed control
    * Monitors individual robot health and operational parameters
4. **Mission Planning & Execution**
    * User creates new mission through missions interface
    * Defines objectives, selects target debris, and configures parameters
    * Initiates mission and monitors progress through real-time tracking
5. **Debris Analysis & Classification**
    * User accesses debris database to review detected objects
    * Filters debris by classification, threat level, and collection priority
    * Reviews AI-powered recommendations for collection strategies
6. **Real-time Mission Monitoring**
    * User monitors active missions through live telemetry feeds
    * Observes 3D visualization of robot movements and debris collection
    * Responds to alerts and adjusts mission parameters as needed
7. **Performance Analysis**
    * User reviews mission outcomes and system performance metrics
    * Analyzes efficiency trends and identifies optimization opportunities
    * Generates reports for stakeholder communication
8. **Training & Simulation**
    * User practices robot control through virtual training scenarios
    * Tests emergency procedures and develops operational proficiency
    * Reviews performance scores and completes certification requirements
9. **System Configuration**
    * User customizes interface preferences and notification settings
    * Configures API integrations and system parameters
    * Manages user account and security settings
10. **Support & Documentation**
    * User accesses help resources and tutorial content
    * Contacts support for technical assistance
    * Reviews system documentation and best practices